            <abstract>
                <label>Abstract</label>
                <p>A new distinctive species of the rare Oriental goniacerine genus <italic><tp:taxon-name><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="genus">Awas</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name></italic> Löbl, <italic><tp:taxon-name><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="genus">Awas</tp:taxon-name-part> <tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="species">gigas</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name></italic> <bold>sp. n.</bold>, is described and illustrated, based on three males and fourteen females taken at the Daoyao Shan Natural Reserve in the southern Chinese province of Guangxi. All specimens were collected from colonies of the ant genus <italic><tp:taxon-name><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="genus">Pachycondyla</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name></italic> F. Smith nesting in decomposing woods.</p>
            </abstract>
